## API Endpoints and Technical Implementation

### Key APIs
- **HTTP V2 API**: `https://api2.amplitude.com/2/httpapi` for sending events
- **Identify API**: `https://api2.amplitude.com/identify` for updating user properties
- **Group Identify API**: For creating and updating group properties

### SDK Implementation Examples
- JavaScript: `amplitude.getInstance().logEvent("event_name", {property: "value"})`
- iOS: `Amplitude.instance().logEvent("event_name", withEventProperties: ["property": "value"])`
- Android: `Amplitude.getInstance().logEvent("event_name", JSONObject properties)`

### Domain Proxy Configuration
Users can configure a domain proxy to relay events through their own domain:
```
location /amplitude/ {
    proxy_pass https://api2.amplitude.com/;
    proxy_set_header Host api2.amplitude.com;
}
```

## Feature-Specific Capabilities

### Behavioral Cohorts
- Create cohorts based on user actions within specific time periods
- Apply cohorts as segments in charts
- Track cohort population changes over time
- Compare metrics between different cohorts

### Account-Level Reporting
- Analyze metrics at the group level rather than individual users
- Create and update group properties
- Define multiple group types for different organizational structures
- Perform group-level analyses for B2B use cases

### Anomaly Detection and Forecasting
- Identify statistically significant deviations in metrics
- Project future trends based on historical patterns
- Configure sensitivity levels (95%, 98%, or 99% confidence intervals)
- Set up automated alerts for anomalies

### Session Replay
- View recorded user sessions with synchronized event streams
- Filter replays by user properties or behaviors
- Troubleshoot issues and understand user experience
- Integrate with quantitative analytics for context